<Class name="CM_AuditAgent" id="d7db249c-0447-4b57-b031-6cf39667641f">
    <superclass name="CM_Agent"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
The CM_AuditAgent handles the auditing of creates, updates and deletes to the
classes specified in the "isAnAuditedClass" method.  To setup a class for auditing
you should to the following:

1.  Add an "allAuditObjects" (CM_AuditObjectDictByTimestamp) collection to the class.
	(inverse back to CM_AuditObject.mySubject).
2.  Add class to "getAuditConfigForClass" of CM_AuditAgent
3.  Reimplement a "getAuditText" method to the class if you want other details audited eg collections. Some collections need to reimplement CM_ObjectArray::auditIdDisplay method.
    Test by displaying getAuditText for an object to see what is returned for that object.
4.  Reimplement a "shouldAuditProperty" method to the class as necassary to select property to exclude from auditting
5.  Reimplement "auditId" method to class
6.  Reimplement "getAuditTextForProperty" to write out differing values for a property
7.  Add the following code to the "delete" method of the class:

		foreach audit in self.allAuditObjects do
			// Tell the audit that it's subject is about to be deleted
			audit.subjectBeingDeleted;
			// Null the reference back to us
			audit.setSubject(null);
		endforeach;
		
8. Add the following code to the following method

CM_UtilityCreateAgent:utlcreateXXX

if _passport.noErrors then
		self.myCreateAuditAgent.audCreateGeneric(_newXXX);
	endif;		
(note XXX---&gt;is the event your are auditing)


9. Add the following code to the following method

CM_UtilityCreateAgent:utlUpdateXXX



	if _passport.noErrors then
		// This is only required if the class is being auditted
		self.myUpdateAuditAgent.audUpdateGeneric(realXXX, true);
	endif;

	if _passport.noErrors then
		realXXX.setForUpdate(_pxyXXX);
	endif;

	if _passport.noErrors then
		// This is only required if the class is being auditted
		self.myUpdateAuditAgent.audUpdateGeneric(realXXX, false);
	endif;
	
	
	(note XXX---&gt;is the event your are auditing)


Refer to one of the existing audited classes for examples of how to use.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="cmtrans"/>
